body:
I run this code in playground:
```
use std::ops::{Deref, DerefMut};
use std::ptr::drop_in_place;

#[repr(transparent)]
pub struct Box1<T: 'static> {
    ptr: &'static mut T,
}

impl<T> Box1<T> {
    pub fn new(ptr: &'static mut T) -> Self {
        Self { ptr: ptr }
    }

    #[inline]
    pub fn as_ptr(self) -> &'static mut T {
        self.ptr
    }
}

impl<T: 'static> Deref for Box1<T> {
    type Target = T;

    #[inline]
    fn deref(&self) -> &T {
        self.ptr
    }
}

impl<T: 'static> DerefMut for Box1<T> {
    #[inline]
    fn deref_mut(&mut self) -> &mut T {
        self.ptr
    }
}

impl<T> Drop for Box1<T> {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        //Call destructor of T (if exists)
        let ptr = self.deref_mut();
        unsafe {
            drop_in_place(ptr);
        }
    }
}

fn main() {

}
```
[link](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=404c03a7cb62ef437a1fded4028d8ac2)

And I got very detailed warning:
```
warning[E0713]: borrow may still be in use when destructor runs
  --> src/main.rs:16:9
   |
16 |         self.ptr
   |         ^^^^^^^^ returning this value requires that `*self.ptr` is borrowed for `'static`
17 |     }
   |     - here, drop of `self` needs exclusive access to `*self.ptr`, because the type `Box1<T>` implements the `Drop` trait
   |
   = warning: This error has been downgraded to a warning for backwards compatibility with previous releases.
           It represents potential unsoundness in your code.
           This warning will become a hard error in the future.
```

But on Nightly (rustc 1.31.0-nightly (78ff609d7 2018-10-19)) I don't get warning or error.

Sometimes I got error when use `deref_mut` or `as_ptr` in my code, but I could not to reproduce it in small code.

P.S. Likely I must use mem::forget in `as_ptr` function. I understand it only when run Playground and got warning.
